feat(notifications): split discord-builder + 4-section structure for 5 channels

Implements 6-Pre 3 (Discord 5-channel content overhaul) per the planned roadmap.

Changes:
- New module src/lib/notifications/discord-builder.ts (5 builders)
- New dictionary src/lib/notifications/discord-strings.ko.json (87 strings)
- src/lib/discord.ts slimmed to sender + helpers; re-exports builders for back-compat
- Removed orphan src/lib/crawler/domemae-parser.ts (work principle #34)
- New scripts/verify-korean-dict.py for ongoing Korean integrity checks
- Updated scripts/test-discord-5-channels.mjs to load dictionary directly

Each embed now follows a 4-section structure:
1) Situation (what happened)
2) Impact   (so what)
3) Action   (concrete next steps with deep links)
4) Kkotti   (mascot voice — cowgirl-garden tone)

Korean text safety pattern (work principle #29 hardening):
- All user-facing Korean lives in a single JSON dictionary.
- Builder code contains zero Korean literals or escape sequences.
- This 100% prevents jamo-corruption typos that occur when the model
  generates Korean escape codes directly. Verified via verify-korean-dict.py
  against 21 known-typo patterns plus NFC and replacement-char checks.

Verification:
- TSC --noEmit: 0 errors
- npm run build: 26/26 prerender OK
- 5-channel live send: all HTTP 204
- Korean integrity: 87 strings, 0 NFC violations, 0 known typos

Sender username corrected from "Kkotti" (English) to "꼬띠" (Korean) in test script
to match production sendDiscord behavior.

Refs: docs/plan/PROGRESS.md, docs/plan/ROADMAP.md
